  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering generally involves financial transactions designed to conceal the origins of illegally obtained money. Legal definitions typically involve three key stages:\n\n1. Placement - introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering - conducting complex financial transactions to obscure the money's source\n3. Integration - reintroducing the \"cleaned\" money into legitimate economic activities\n\nSpecific legal definitions vary by jurisdiction, but most include:\n- Knowingly converting/transferring assets derived from criminal activity\n- Concealing the true nature/origin of illegally obtained funds\n- Attempting to make illegal funds appear legal\n- Participating in transactions to hide criminal proceeds\n\nPenalties often include:\n- Significant financial fines\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Asset forfeiture\n\nFor precise legal details, I recommend consulting specific national/state statutes or legal professionals.",
